data.title: Nice Irish Bar
data.text: I ducked in here to beat the heat during the wine festival and I am glad I did.  They have a great selection of draft beers at the ling old bar.  The other half of the place is for food which appears to be German.  We just drank and watched football.  Our bartender was nice and pint beers were $4.  I would go back here in a flash.

data.title: Great place.
data.text: Irish drink, German food, hard to go wrong. Murphy's Law is a nice, lay back place to hang out and a credit to the continually developing downtown Bryan area.

data.title: Taste of Germany
data.text:
My second visit and family's first.   
Following. My recommendation we tried it but the seasoning in the veal was rather bland.    We normally eat poem schnitzel but opted for better meat.   Not a great choice.   

Service was very good until we ordered desert.    Took about 15 minutes for store bought cake and made to order crepes.    Crepes were the drag on the order.   

But decent.

data.title: A good local Irish Pub
data.text: I visited Murphy's Law with my husband and a friend. This place is your quintessential American Irish Pub. The place was very clean and had plenty of open seating. We came on a Friday night around 11 PM and it wasn't packed. The beer selection isn't that great but they do have you standard Irish beers. This is a scene for young locals. They have trivia night on Thursdays. They are also connected to the Brauhause, a German restaurant. They also have TVs for sports. I would recommend checking this place out.

data.title: Great Food & Great Atmosphere
data.text: I feel like I have left Texas & am in a pub in Ireland. Great atmosphere & incredible food. A perfect escape.

data.title: Rude Bartenders, Never Again
data.text: A person in town recommended I go to this bar to avoid the college kids in College Station. I went with 2 friends of mine visiting from San Antonio that drove up to welcome me to Texas (I just moved here). I ordered a beer and gave the bartender my military dependant ID and he refused to take it and said he needed a driver license because the owner prefers them. I just got a new one so all I had was the paper print out the DMV gave me that was in my car. I brought it in, got my drink, and sat down. It was pretty dead, the music was meh, and they had a mixed crowd. I got up to get another drink this time just showing my paper print out of my new TX license. This bartender (different one) decided he didn't like it and that I'd need another ID, so I showed him my military ID. I don't know if those 2 guys were idiots or just rude but I will never go to that bar again. This is a college town filled with people from all over the world, chances are we're going to have a form of ID other than a driver license!

data.title: My family and I went to celebrate St. Patrick's Day tonight.
data.text:
Our desire to an Irish meal ended up as a great disappointment. The fish & Chips were great  but the cheese burger had no cheese and the Corned Beef and Cabbage had neither corned beef or cabbage. What a great disaster in two meals. And the malt cinder vinegar? The server eventually found one bottle and it was close to empty.
Sad!!
The German meals have repeatedly been great. What happened?

data.title: great, authentic food!
data.text: My boyfriend and I were attracted to this place by its unique menu and we were not disappointed! He had schnitzel and I had the German "mac n cheese" (I can't remember the German word!).  We also shared a kind of appetizer sampler platter. There was so much food, we couldn't finish it all! The meatballs were excellent and the potato salad was as well.  There was nothing we didn't like. The only thing that was a drawback was the people smoking inside...
